## Diagnosis

The two-axis grammar (color channel + weight channel) is correctly structured but both axes are miscalibrated. The resting state is rendering at 2px — the same visual weight as the engaged state — collapsing the distinction between the two. The weight channel is not doing its job: resting should be a hairline (1px), engaged should promote to 2px via the paint-only ring overlay.

**Root Cause: AP-072** — *Axis value drift under iterative patching.* Each successive fix adjusted the mechanism without auditing the concrete pixel values on both axes simultaneously, allowing the weight channel's resting value to creep upward until it matched the engaged value, making the two states visually identical.

---

## Fix

### 1. Design token correction — `tokens/components/input.css`

```css
/* tokens/components/input.css */

@layer elan.tokens {
  :root {
    /* ── Color channel (what color is the border) ───────────────── */
    --input-border-color-resting:  var(--color-neutral-300);
    --input-border-color-hovered:  var(--color-neutral-400);
    --input-border-color-engaged:  var(--color-brand-500);
    --input-border-color-invalid:  var(--color-error-500);
    --input-border-color-disabled: var(--color-neutral-200);

    /* ── Weight channel (how thick is the border) ───────────────── */
    --input-border-width-resting:  1px;   /* hairline — was wrongly 2px */
    --input-border-width-engaged:  2px;   /* promoted weight on focus   */

    /* ── Ring offset so the 2px ring doesn't shift layout ──────── */
    --input-ring-offset: 0px;             /* paint-only, no layout cost */
  }
}
```

---

### 2. Component styles — `components/input/input.css`

```css
/* components/input/input.css */

@layer elan.components {

  .input {
    /* Color channel — resting */
    border-width: var(--input-border-width-resting);   /* 1px */
    border-style: solid;
    border-color: var(--input-border-color-resting);

    /* Prevent layout shift when the engaged ring appears */
    outline: var(--input-border-width-engaged) solid transparent;
    outline-offset: calc(-1 * var(--input-border-width-engaged));

    border-radius: var(--input-radius);
    transition:
      border-color  120ms ease,
      outline-color 120ms ease;
  }

  /* ── Hover: color channel only, weight stays hairline ─────────── */
  .input:hover:not(:focus):not(:disabled) {
    border-color: var(--input-border-color-hovered);
  }

  /* ── Engaged: color channel + promote weight via paint-only ring ─ */
  .input:focus-visible {
    border-color:  var(--input-border-color-engaged);

    /*
     * The outline paints 2px inset, covering the 1px border pixel
     * and adding 1px more — net visual weight 2px, zero layout shift.
     */
    outline-color: var(--input-border-color-engaged);
  }

  /* ── Invalid ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .input[aria-invalid="true"] {
    border-color: var(--input-border-color-invalid);
  }

  .input[aria-invalid="true"]:focus-visible {
    outline-color: var(--input-border-color-invalid);
  }

  /* ── Disabled: color channel only, weight stays hairline ─────── */
  .input:disabled {
    border-color: var(--input-border-color-disabled);
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }
}
```

---

### 3. Storybook story — audit all five states visually `Input.stories.tsx`

Add a dedicated **WeightAxis** story so any future regression is immediately visible in the canvas without reading code:

```tsx
// components/input/Input.stories.tsx

export const WeightAxis: Story = {
  name: "⚖ Weight axis — resting 1px / engaged 2px",
  render: () => (
    <div style={{ display: "flex", flexDirection: "column", gap: "1rem", width: 320 }}>
      {(
        [
          ["resting",  false, false, false],
          ["hovered",  false, false, false],   // inspect via DevTools hover
          ["engaged",  true,  false, false],
          ["invalid",  false, true,  false],
          ["disabled", false, false, true ],
        ] as const
      ).map(([label, focused, invalid, disabled]) => (
        <label key={label} style={{ display: "flex", flexDirection: "column", gap: 4 }}>
          <span style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#666" }}>
            {label} — border should be {focused ? "2px" : "1px"}
          </span>
          <input
            className="input"
            defaultValue={label}
            // eslint-disable-next-line jsx-a11y/no-autofocus
            autoFocus={focused}
            aria-invalid={invalid || undefined}
            disabled={disabled}
            readOnly
          />
        </label>
      ))}
    </div>
  ),
};
```

---

## Why the outline trick is the right mechanism

| Concern | Border alone | Border + inset outline |
|---|---|---|
| Layout shift on weight change | Yes — 1→2px pushes siblings | **No** — outline is paint-only |
| Supports color channel independently | Yes | Yes |
| Weight channel is independently auditable | Yes | **Yes — outline-color: transparent shows the slot** |
| Browser support | Universal | Universal (outline has been inset-capable since 2022 across all evergreens) |

---

## Principle

**Two-axis grammar requires two independently audited value sets.** Whenever you touch one axis (color), explicitly re-read and assert the other axis (weight) in the same commit. The resting weight is the baseline contract; every other state is a delta from it. If the baseline drifts, all deltas become meaningless.
